hi
Hello! How can I assist you today?
My campaign is active, but I don't know where to optimize it. Can you help me?

Sure, I can help with that! To optimize your campaign, you can start by reviewing the ad performance in the Reporting tab. Look for insights on what works and what doesn't. You can refine your audience targeting, schedule ads during peak hours, and invest in visually compelling ad content. Additionally, running A/B tests to identify which ad variations perform best is a great strategy before allocating more budget. If you need more detailed guidance, check out this article: [NewsBreak Advertising Cost](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17959734533005-NewsBreak-Advertising-Cost). Let me know if you have any other questions!
Hi i need talk with human
I'm here to help with whatever you need! Let me know your question, and I'll do my best to assist you right away.
where is my Breakdown menu?

The Breakdown menu is typically found in the Reporting section of your NewsBreak dashboard. It allows you to view detailed insights and performance metrics for your campaigns. If you're having trouble locating it, make sure you're logged into your account and navigate to the Reporting tab. Let me know if you need further assistance!
im conected, but dont have Breakdown menu

If you're connected and still don't see the Breakdown menu, it might be due to a display issue or account permissions. Try refreshing your browser or clearing your cache. If the problem persists, please reach out to our support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance. They'll be able to look into your account settings and help resolve the issue.
